<body>
    <h1>JSON output</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"JSONoutput-Description">Description</h1>=20
<p>Json output step allows to generate json blocks based on input step valu=
es. Output json will be available as java script array or java script objec=
t depends on step settings.</p>=20
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper"><img class=3D"confluenc=
e-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border" src=3D"40d677df15f9ca6138=
40274dfbbfa518" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/25043814/jsonOUt.pn=
g?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1389172351000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unres=
olved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"25166028" data-linked-=
resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked=
-resource-default-alias=3D"jsonOUt.png" data-base-url=3D"https://wiki.penta=
ho.com" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resourc=
e-container-id=3D"25043814" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"21" w=
idth=3D"468" height=3D"120"></span></p>=20
<p><a href=3D"/download/attachments/25043814/json_output.ktr?version=3D1&am=
p;modificationDate=3D1389259055000&amp;api=3Dv2" data-linked-resource-id=3D=
"25166029" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"=
attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"json_output.ktr" data-lin=
ked-resource-content-type=3D"application/octet-stream" data-linked-resource=
-container-id=3D"25043814" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"21">Tr=
ansformation with json output usage example</a></p>=20
<h1 id=3D"JSONoutput-Options">Options</h1>=20
<h2 id=3D"JSONoutput-GeneralTab">General Tab</h2>=20
<p>General tab allows to specify type of step operation, output json struct=
ure, step output file. This file will be used to dump all generated json.</=
p>=20
<h3 id=3D"JSONoutput-Settings">Settings</h3>=20
<p>See detailed settings description below.</p>=20
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>=20
<tr>=20
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p> Option </p></th>=20
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p> Description </p></th>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Step name </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Step name should be unique in context of tra=
nsformation <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Operation </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Specify step operation type. Currently avail=
able 3 types of operation: <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"></p>=20
<ol>=20
<li>Output value - only pass output json as a step output field, do not dum=
p to output file</li>=20
<li>Write to file - only write to fie, do not pass to output field</li>=20
<li>Output value and write to file - dump to file and pass generated json a=
s a step output file <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"></li>=20
</ol> </td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Json block name <br class=3D"atl-forced-newl=
ine"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> This value will be used as a name for json b=
lock. Can be empty string that will affect output json structure, see detai=
led description below. <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Nr. rows in a block </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Number of json block key - value pairs. <br =
class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> NOTE, 1 is a special values, in case of 1 eve=
ry output will be generated as one object. See description below. <br class=
=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Output value <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline=
"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> This value will be used as a step output fie=
ld. Will contain generated json output block depending on step settings. <b=
r class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Compatibility mode <br class=3D"atl-forced-n=
ewline"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> This check box handles compatibility configu=
ration with previous Kettle versions (before PDI 4.3.0 if checked, after PD=
I 4.3.0 otherwise) <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
</tbody>
</table>
</div>=20
<p>Compatibility mode was introduced since PDI 4.3.0 version. This was desi=
gned to handle fix with changes to json structure generation. By default ne=
w fixed mode is used. To enable compatibility mode check 'Compatibility mod=
e' check box.</p>=20
<p>For example step has a row input data with 2 fields: field "name" with s=
tring value "item" and field "value" with numeric value 25. We have 4 rows =
of data with "name" and "value".&nbsp;</p>=20
<p>Consider Json output step has settings combination:</p>=20
<ul>=20
<li>'Json block name' =3D "data"</li>=20
<li>'Nr rows in block' =3D 3</li>=20
<li>'Compatibility mode' NOT checked (and this is the default option)</li>=
=20
</ul>=20
<p>step will generate output:</p>=20
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>{
&nbsp; "data" : [ {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }, {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }, {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; } ]
}{
&nbsp; "data" : [ {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; } ]
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
<p>So We have 2 objects, first object has a 'data' (Json block name) array =
contains 3 json objects (because of number rows in a block is 3) and second=
 object with array contains only one object. 3+1 is actually 4 rows process=
ed.</p>=20
<p>If compatibility mode is enabled and step has settings combination like:=
</p>=20
<ul>=20
<li>Json block name =3D "data"</li>=20
<li>Nr rows in block =3D 3</li>=20
<li>'Compatibility mode' <span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;">is che=
cked</span></li>=20
</ul>=20
<p>step will generate output:</p>=20
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>{"data":[{"name":"item"},{"value":25},{"name":"item"},{"value":25},{"n=
ame":"item"},{"value":25}]}
{"data":[{"name":"item"},{"value":25}]}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
<p>Pretty formatting does not affect compatibility mode. We have 2 output j=
son objects. First object harvest first 3 input rows and second object harv=
ests only one row. This happens because of number of rows in a block is 3. =
Anyway it can be considered as incorrect result, as the real object count f=
or array is 6 for the first output object. By default compatibility mode is=
 disabled.</p>=20
<p>If <span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;">'Json block name' is an e=
mpty string</span> (by default it has 'data' value) - compatibility mode wi=
ll use empty string for block name. Normally - if compatibility mode was no=
t checked, step output will be:</p>=20
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>[ {
&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp; "value" : 25
}, {
&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp; "value" : 25
}, {
&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp; "value" : 25
} ][ {
&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp; "value" : 25
} ]</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
<p>So we have 2 json arrays, first array contains 3 items, second array con=
tains one item.</p>=20
<p>Another special case is when 'Nr. rows in a block' =3D 1.<br> If used wi=
th empty json block name output will looks like:</p>=20
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>{
&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp; "value" : 25
}{
&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp; "value" : 25
}{
&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp; "value" : 25
}{
&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp; "value" : 25
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
<p>We will have just 4 simple json objects that will be outputted as a 4 st=
ep output rows.</p>=20
<p>In case of json block name is defined - output structure will looks like=
:</p>=20
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>{
&nbsp; "data" : {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }
}{
&nbsp; "data" : {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }
}{
&nbsp; "data" : {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }
}{
&nbsp; "data" : {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
<p>So this is will be same 4 output objects with json block name defined.</=
p>=20
<p>If 'Nr. rows in a block' will be less that 1 output will be as a one obj=
ect:</p>=20
<div class=3D"preformatted panel" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"preformattedContent panelContent">=20
<pre>{
&nbsp; "data" : [ {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }, {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }, {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; }, {
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "name" : "item",
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "value" : 25
&nbsp; } ]
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
<p>This will be one object (one output row) with data block containing json=
 array with 4 objects (as we had 4 input data rows). Please note - when usi=
ng 0 'Nr. rows in a block' step will build output object until input data i=
s available. When input is done - one big output object will be passed to o=
utput row. For big input data it can impact memory usage.</p>=20
<h3 id=3D"JSONoutput-OutputFile">Output File</h3>=20
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>=20
<tr>=20
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p> Option </p></th>=20
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p> Description </p></th>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Filename </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> full path to output file <br class=3D"atl-fo=
rced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Append <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p=
></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> If not checked new file will be created ever=
y time step is running. If file with specified name already existed - it wi=
ll be replaced by a new one. If checked - new json output will be appended =
at the end of existing file. Or if existing file is not exists - it will be=
 created as in previous case. <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=
=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Create Parent folder <br class=3D"atl-forced=
-newline"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Usually file name contains some path folder =
as a parent folder. If parent folder does not exists and this option is che=
cked - parent folder will be created as a new folder. Otherwise - file not =
be found and step will fail. <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Do not open create at start <br class=3D"atl=
-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> If not checked - file (and in some cases par=
ent folder) will be created/opened to write during transformation initializ=
ation. If checked - file and parent folder will be created only after step =
will get any first input data. <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=
=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Extension <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> =
</p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Output file extension. Default value is 'js'=
 <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Encoding <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> <=
/p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Output file encoding <br class=3D"atl-forced=
-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Pass output to servlet <br class=3D"atl-forc=
ed-newline"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Enable this option to return the data via a =
web service instead writing into a file (see <a href=3D"/display/EAI/PDI+da=
ta+over+web+services">PDI data over web service</a>) <br class=3D"atl-force=
d-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Include date in filename? <br class=3D"atl-f=
orced-newline"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> If checked - output file name will contains =
File name value + current date. This may help to generate unique output fil=
es. <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Include time in filename <br class=3D"atl-fo=
rced-newline"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> If checked - output file name will contains =
file creation time. Same as for 'Include date in filename' option <br class=
=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Show filename(s) button <br class=3D"atl-for=
ced-newline"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Can be useful to test full output file path =
<br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Add file to result filenames? <br class=3D"a=
tl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> If checked - created output file path will b=
e accessible form step result <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=
=20
</tr>=20
</tbody>
</table>
</div>=20
<h2 id=3D"JSONoutput-FieldsTab">Fields Tab</h2>=20
<p>This tab is used to map input step fields to output json values</p>=20
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>=20
<tr>=20
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p> Option </p></th>=20
<th class=3D"confluenceTh"><p> Description </p></th>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Fieldname </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Input step field name. Use 'Get Fields' butt=
on to discover available input fields <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p=
></td>=20
</tr>=20
<tr>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Element name <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline=
"> </p></td>=20
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p> Json element name as a key. For example "A":=
"B" - A is a element name, B is actual input value mapped for this Element =
name. <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> </p></td>=20
</tr>=20
</tbody>
</table>
</div>=20
<h1 id=3D"JSONoutput-MetadataInjectionSupport">Metadata Injection Support</=
h1>=20
<p>All fields of this step support metadata injection. You can use this ste=
p with <a href=3D"https://help.pentaho.com/Documentation/8.0/Products/Data_=
Integration/Transformation_Step_Reference/ETL_Metadata_Injection" class=3D"=
external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ETL Metadata Injection</a> to pass metadata=
 to your transformation at runtime.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
